	h3 4 February, Saturday (Week 1) - Welcome Home
	.story #[.ellis] It has been exactly a week since the D-Day. I am still looking at the photos of Audrey in her first hour of arrival. It seems like her face changes every day and I can't catch up. I must say the first week is horrible. I always know that when we introduce a new activity in our lifestyle, there bound to be time needed to settle down. I once experienced it when I first moved in to Elvin's house after married. It took us a while to get the routine back and be able to do things at the most efficient way. 

