	h3 18 February, Saturday (Week 3) - Making Sounds and Flipping Tummies
	.subline Head circumference: 35 cm. Body Length: 48 cm.
	
	.story #[.ellis] It is the third week of my confinement. I am counting down to the end of it. There are simply too many 'rules' aka old wives' tales that are too hard to follow. For example, one of them is that the mother cannot touch water. So how am I going to wash the bottles? And for the 'cannot shower' part, I totally ignored because my rash came back, big time. I need to keep clean, so I have to shower. If any of the tales came true, I shall update during my old age. Haha. 

