	.story At night, we take turns to wake up to make milk for her. Sometimes I am so sleepy, I don't hear her crying for food. That poor little girl. She is so tired and yet her hunger wakes her into a wail. When I am making the milk, my sleepy eyes can hardly see the markings on the milk bottle as I try to pour 90 ml of water. Add three scoops of milk powder and milk is ready for Audrey. Thank god for formula milk.

	.story My favourite activity with Audrey this week is "Flipping Tummies". It is where I flip her on her tummy and she rest on mine. I can feel tiny heart beating rapidly against my chest. She squirms around as she tries to make sense of this new experience. After a while, she falls asleep. Other times, I flip her on a tummy and give her a back massage. Lying on her back the whole time mustn't be fun so this should give her some relief. Once she fell asleep during the massage.
